The paper presents a new scalable parallelization scheme for generating the 3D Delaunay triangulation of a given set of points. This involves efficient serial implementation, multi-threaded version of the Delaunay kernel, and integration in a Delaunay refinement mesh generator. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.MS (Mathematical Software), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
